<item>
            <title>[PIG-1921] Improve error messages in new parser</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1921</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The new parser gives better error messages than the old parser (especially with the line numbers). But there are still some places where the error messages can be improved.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
ERROR org.apache.pig.tools.grunt.Grunt - ERROR 1025: Invalid field projection. Projected field [E::v] does not exist in schema: A::v#28:&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt;,A::u#29:chararray,A::w#30:bytearray,B::v#31:&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;long&lt;/span&gt;,B::u#32:chararray,B::w#33:bytearray.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this case the #num should be removed from the schema.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
ERROR org.apache.pig.tools.grunt.Grunt - ERROR 0: line 5:34 mismatched input [&apos;&apos;reg&apos;&apos;] expecting set &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this case the parser detects the error early and gives the line number, but missing the reason part from the old parser message:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
ERROR org.apache.pig.tools.grunt.Grunt - ERROR 1000: Error during parsing. Only COLLECTED, REGULAR or MERGE are valid GROUP modifiers.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
grunt&amp;gt; C = join A by v, B by A.t;
2011-03-18 14:04:38,441 [main] ERROR org.apache.pig.tools.grunt.Grunt - ERROR 0: Invalid scalar projection: A
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this case the real reason is t is not a field of A : &lt;/p&gt;
{v: int, u:int}
&lt;p&gt;. So the message should be: Invalid scalar projection: A.t&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
C = join A by v, B by B::A.v;
2011-03-18 14:40:11,590 [main] ERROR org.apache.pig.tools.grunt.Grunt - ERROR 1000: Invalid field reference. Referenced field [v] does not exist in schema: &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The message here is not clear and the schema shouldn&apos;t be null.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
